Data Citation: https://www.nbastuffer.com/2020-2021-nba-player-stats/

- Full Name: Player's full name
- Team: Team name
- POS: The position that the player is in
- AGE: Player's age
- GP: Total number of games played in the season
- MPG: The average number of minutes a player has played per game
- MIN%: Percentage of team minutes used by a player while he was on the floor
- USG%: The percentage of team plays used by a player when they are on
- TO%:  A metric that estimates the number of turnovers a player commits per 100 possessions
- FTA: The number of free throws that a player has attempted
- FT%:  The percentage of free throw attempts that a player has made successfully
- 2PA: The number of two pointers that a player has attempted
- 2P%: The percentage of points scored by a player that are from 2 point field goals
- 3PA: The number of 3 point field goals that a player has attempted
- 3P%:  The percentage of points scored by a player that are from 3 point field goals
- eFG%: Measures field goal percentage adjusting for made 3-point field goals being 1.5 times more valuable than made 2-point field goals.
- TS%: A shooting percentage that factors in the value of three-point field goals and free throws in addition to conventional two-point field goals
- PPG: Thr average number of points per game that a player will score
- RPG: The number of rebounds a player makes per game
- TRB%:  The estimated percentage of available rebounds grabbed by the player while the player is on the court
- APG: The average number of assists a player makes per game
- AST%: The estimated percentage of teammate field goals a player assisted while the player is on the court
- SPG: The average number of steals a player makes per game
- BPG:The average number of blocks a player makes per game
- TOPG: The average number of turnovers a player makes per game, it is when a team loses possession of the ball to the opposing team
- VI: A metric that measures a playerâ€™s ability to produce in points, assists, and rebounds. The average player will score around a 5 on the index, while top players score above a 10
- ORTG: The number of points produced by a player per 100 total individual possessions
- DRTG: The number of points the player allowed per 100 possessions he individually faced while staying on the court
